isoiec80000:term-t7-1.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "speed of light in a medium"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-1.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "c"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-1.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-1.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-1.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-1.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """phase speed of an electromagnetic wave at a given point in a medium"""@en ;
  skos:note """See also <<iso80000-3>>.

The value of the speed of light in a medium can depend on the frequency, polarization, and direction.

For the definition of the speed of electromagnetic waves in vacuum, stem:[c_0], see <<iso80000-1>>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m*s^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-1.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "refractive index"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-1.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "n"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-1.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-1.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-1.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-1.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of speed of light in vacuum (<<iso80000-1>>) and speed of light in a medium (<<t7-1.1>>)"""@en ;
  skos:note """The value of the refractive index can depend on the frequency, polarization, and direction.

The refractive index is expressed by stem:[n = c_0//c], where stem:[c_0] is the speed of light in vacuum and stem:[c] is the speed of light in the medium.

For a medium with absorption, the complex refractive index stem:[n] is defined by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
n = n + \"i\"k
++++

where stem:[k] is spectral absorption index (<<iec60050-845>>) and stem:[\"i\"] is imaginary unit.

The refractivity is expressed by stem:[n-1], where stem:[n] is refractive index.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-2.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant energy <electromagnetism>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Q_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "W"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "U"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-3 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Q)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-2.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-2.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-2.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-2 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.1-3 ;
  skos:definition """energy (<<iso80000-5>>) emitted, transferred or received in form of electromagnetic waves"""@en ;
  skos:note """Radiant energy can be expressed by the time integral of radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>), stem:[Phi_\"e\"], over a given duration (<<iso80000-3>>), stem:[Delta t]

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Q_\"e\" = int_(Delta t) Phi_\"e\" \"d\"t
++++

Radiant energy is expressed either as a function of wavelength (<<iso80000-3>>), stem:[lambda], as a function of frequency (<<iso80000-3>>), stem:[nu], or as a function of wavenumber, stem:[sigma]. (See also <<cls-0.1>>.)

The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous energy\" (<<t7-12>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon energy\" (<<t7-19.2>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-2.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant energy"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Q_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "W_lambda"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "U_lambda"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-3 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Q_lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-2.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-2.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-2.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-2 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-2.2-3 ;
  skos:definition """spectral density of radiant energy, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Q_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\"Q_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"e\"] is radiant energy (<<t7-2.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The integral of (total) radiant energy is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Q_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2) Q_(\"e\",lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/nm ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-3.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant energy density"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "w"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(rho_\"e\")"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-3.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-3.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-3.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """volumetric density of radiant energy, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
w = (\"d\"Q_\"e\")/(\"d\"V)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"e\"] is radiant energy (<<t7-2.1>>) in an elementary three-dimensional domain and stem:[V] is the volume (<<iso80000-3>>) of that domain
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Radiant energy density within a Planckian radiator is given by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
w = (4 sigma)/c_0 T^4
++++

where stem:[sigma] is the Stefan-Boltzmann constant (<<iso80000-1>>), stem:[c_0] is speed of light in vacuum (<<iso80000-1>>) and stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<iso80000-5>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/m^3 ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^(-1)*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-3.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant energy density in terms of wavelength"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "w_lambda"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-3.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-3.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-3.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """change of radiant energy density with wavelength, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
w_lambda = (\"d\"w)/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[w] is radiant energy density (<<t7-3.1>>) as a function of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Spectral radiant energy density within a Planckian radiator is given by stem:[w_lambda = 8 pi h c_0 * f(lambda, T)], where stem:[h] is the Planck constant (<<iso80000-1>>), stem:[c_0] is speed of light in vacuum (<<iso80000-1>>), stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<iso80000-5>) and

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
f(lambda,T) = (lambda^(-5))/(\"exp\"(c_2 lambda^(-1)T^(-1))-1)
++++

For the radiation constant stem:[c_2] in stem:[f(lambda, T)], see <<iso80000-1>>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/(m^3*nm) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^(-2)*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-3.3-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant energy density in terms of wavenumber"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.3-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "w_(tilde nu)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.3-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "rho_(tilde nu)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-3.3 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-3.3" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-3.3-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.3-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-3.3-1 ;
  skos:definition """change of radiant energy density with wavenumber, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
w_(tilde nu) = (\"d\"w)/(\"d\"tilde nu)
++++

where stem:[w] is radiant energy density (<<t7-3.1>>) as a function of wavenumber stem:[tilde nu] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/m^2 ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-4.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant flux"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-4.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant power"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Phi_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "P_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.1-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Phi, P)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-4.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-4.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-4.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-4.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.1-2 ;
  skos:definition """change in radiant energy with time, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"e\" = (\"d\"Q_\"e\")/(\"d\"t)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"e\"] is the radiant energy (<<t7-2.1>>) emitted, transferred or received and stem:[t] is time (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous flux\" (<<t7-13>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon flux\" (<<t7-20>>)."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-3) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-4.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant flux"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-4.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant power"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Phi_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "P_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.2-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Phi_lambda, P_lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-4.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-4.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-4.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-4.2-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.2-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-4.2-2 ;
  skos:definition """spectral density of radiant flux, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\" Phi_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"e\"] is radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The integral of (total) radiant flux is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2) Phi_(\"e\",lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/nm ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m*s^(-3) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-5.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant intensity"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "I_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(I)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-5.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-5.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-5.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of radiant flux with respect to solid angle in a specified direction, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
I_\"e\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"e\")/(\"d\"Omega)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"e\"] is the radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) emitted in a specified direction, and stem:[Omega] is the solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) containing that direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The definition holds strictly only for a point source.

The distribution of the radiant intensities as a function of the direction of emission, e.g. given by the polar angles stem:[(vartheta,varphi)], is used to determine the radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) within a certain solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>), stem:[Omega], of a source:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"e\" = &#8748;_Omega I_\"e\" (vartheta,varphi) \"sin\" vartheta \"d\" varphi \"d\" vartheta
++++

The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous intensity\" (<<t7-14>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon intensity\" (<<t7-21>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/sr ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-3)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-5.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant intensity"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "I_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(I_lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-5.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-5.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-5.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-5.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """spectral density of radiant intensity, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
I_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\"I_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[I_\"e\"] is radiant intensity (<<t7-5.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The integral of (total) radiant intensity is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
I_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2) I_(\"e\",lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/(sr*nm) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m*s^(-3)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-6.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "L_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(L)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-6.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-6.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-6.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of radiant intensity with respect to projected area in a specified direction at a specified point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"e\" = (\"d\"l_\"e\")/(\"d\"A) 1/(\"cos\"alpha)
++++

where stem:[I_\"e\"] is radiant intensity (<<t7-5.1>>), A is area (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[alpha] is the angle between the normal to the surface at the specified point and the specified direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """See also <<cls-0.1>>.

For Planckian radiation,

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"e\" = sigma/pi T^4
++++

where stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<iso80000-5>>) and stem:[sigma] is the Stefan-Boltzmann constant (<<iso80000-1>>).

The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminance\" (<<t7-15>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon radiance\" (<<t7-22>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/(sr*m^2) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*s^(-3)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-6.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "L_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(L_lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-6.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-6.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-6.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-6.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of radiance with respect to wavelength, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\"L_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[L_\"e\"] is radiance (<<t7-6.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """For Planckian radiation,

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda) = (c(lambda))/(4pi) omega_lambda (lambda) = hc_0^2*f(lambda,T)
++++

where stem:[c(lambda)] is phase speed (<<iso80000-3>>) of electromagnetic radiation of a wavelength (<<iso80000-3>>) stem:[lambda] in a given medium, stem:[omega_lambda(lambda)] is spectral radiant energy density in terms of wavelength, stem:[c_0] is speed of light in vacuum (<<iso80000-1>>), stem:[h] is the Planck constant (<<iso80000-1>>), and

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
f(lambda,T) = (lambda^(-5))/(\"exp\"(c_2 lambda^(-1)T^(-1))-1)
++++

where the radiation constant stem:[c_2 = hc//k].

The integral of (total) radiance is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2)L_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/(sr*m^2*nm) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^(-1)*s^(-3)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-7.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "irradiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "E_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(E)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-7.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-7.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-7.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of incident radiant flux with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_\"e\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"e\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"e\"] is radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) on which the radiant flux is incident
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding photometric quantity is \"illuminance\" (<<t7-16>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon irradiance\" (<<t7-23>>).

The quantity \"spherical irradiance\" is defined by the mean value of irradiance on the outer curved surface of a very small (real or imaginary) sphere at a point in space.

It can be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_(\"e\",0) = int_(4pi)L_\"e\" \"d\"Omega
++++

where stem:[Omega] is solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) and stem:[L_\"e\"] is radiance (<<t7-6.1>>).

(See <<cie017,locality:term=\"17-21-054\">>.)

It can be expressed by the quotient of the radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) of all the radiation incident on the outer surface of an infinitely small sphere centred at the specified point and the area (<<iso80000-3>>) of the diametrical cross-section of that sphere.

Spherical irradiance is also called \"fluence rate\" or \"radiant fluence rate\".

The corresponding photometric quantity to spherical irradiance is called \"spherical illuminance\".
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/m^2 ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*s^(-3) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-7.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral irradiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "E_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(E_lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-7.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-7.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-7.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-7.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of irradiance with respect to wavelength, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\"E_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[E_\"e\"] is irradiance (<<t7-7.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The integral of (total) irradiance is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2) E_(\"e\",lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/(m^2*nm) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^(-1)*s^(-3) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-8.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant exitance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-8.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "DEPRECATED: radiant emittance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "M_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(M)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-8.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-8.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-8.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-8.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of exiting radiant flux with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
M_\"e\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"e\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"e\"] is radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) from which the radiant flux leaves
"""@en ;
  skos:note """For Planckian radiation, stem:[M_\"e\" = sigma T^4] where stem:[T] is thermodynamic temperature (<<iso80000-5>>) and stem:[sigma] is the Stefan-Boltzmann constant (<<iso80000-1>>).

The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous exitance\" (<<t7-17>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon exitance\" (<<t7-24>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/m^2 ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*s^(-3) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-8.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant exitance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "M_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(M_(lambda))"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-8.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-8.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-8.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-8.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of radiant exitance with respect to wavelength, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
M_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\"M_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[M_\"e\"] is radiant exitance (<<t7-8.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The integral of (total) radiant exitance is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
M_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2) M_(\"e\",lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-W/(m^2*nm) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^(-1)*s^(-3) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-9.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiant exposure"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "H_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(H)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-9.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-9.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-9.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of incident radiant energy with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H_\"e\" = (\"d\"Q_\"e\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"e\"] is radiant energy (<<t7-2.1>>) and stem:[A] is the area on which the radiant energy is incident (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous exposure\" (<<t7-18>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon exposure\" (<<t7-25>>)."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/m^2 ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-9.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral radiant exposure"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "H_(\"e\",lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(H_lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-9.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-9.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-9.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-9.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of radiant exposure with respect to wavelength, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H_(\"e\",lambda) = (\"d\"H_\"e\")/(\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[H_\"e\"] is radiant exposure (<<t7-9.1>>) in terms of wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The integral of (total) radiant exposure is determined by the wavelength interval stem:[(lambda_1, lambda_2)] under consideration:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H_\"e\" = int_(lambda_1)^(lambda_2) H_(\"e\",lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J/(m^2*nm) ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^(-1)*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-10.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous efficiency <specified photometric condition>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-10.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "V"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-10.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-10.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-10.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-10.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) weighted by the spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>) and the corresponding radiant flux for a specified photometric condition"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminous efficiency for photopic vision is expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
V = (int_0^(oo)Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda)/(int_0^(oo)Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)\"d\"lambda) = K/K_\"m\"
++++

where stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)] is spectral radiant flux (<<t7-4.2>>), stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency, stem:[lambda] is wavelength, stem:[K] is luminous efficacy of radiation (<<t7-11.1>>), and stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>).

For scotopic and mesopic vision see <<cls-0.4>> and <<cls-0.5>>.

Symbols for different photometric conditions:

stem:[V], <for photopic vision>; stem:[V'], <for scotopic vision>; stem:[V_\"mes;m\"], <for mesopic vision>; stem:[V_(10)], <for the CIE 10&deg; photopic photometric observer>; stem:[V_\"M\"], <for the CIE 1988 modified 2&deg; spectral luminous efficiency function for photopic vision>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-10.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral luminous efficiency <specified photometric condition>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-10.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "V(lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-10.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-10.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-10.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-10.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda_\"m\"] and that at wavelength stem:[lambda], such that both produce equally intense luminous sensations for a specified photometric condition and stem:[lambda_\"m\"] is chosen so that the maximum value of this quotient is equal to 1"""@en ;
  skos:note """The spectral luminous efficiency of the human eye depends on a number of factors, particularly the state of visual adaptation and the size and position of the source in the visual field. The photometric condition should be specified (e.g. photopic, scotopic, mesopic). If it is not specified, photopic vision is assumed and the symbol stem:[V(lambda)] is used.

For scotopic and mesopic vision see <<cls-0.4>> and <<cls-0.5>>.

Symbols for different photometric conditions:

stem:[V(lambda)], <for photopic vision>; stem:[V'(lambda)], <for scotopic vision>; stem:[V_\"mes;m\"(lambda)], <for mesopic vision>; stem:[V_(10)(lambda)], <for the CIE 10&deg; photopic photometric observer>; stem:[V_\"M\"(lambda)], <for the CIE 1988 modified 2&deg; spectral luminous efficiency function for photopic vision>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-11.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous efficacy of radiation <specified photometric condition>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "K"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-11.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-11.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-11.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and the corresponding radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) for a specified photometric condition"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminous efficacy of radiation for photopic vision is expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
K = (Phi_\"v\")/(Phi_\"e\")
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v\"] is luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[Phi_\"e\"] is radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>).

For scotopic and mesopic vision see <<cls-0.4>> and <<cls-0.5>>.

Symbols for different photometric conditions:

stem:[K], <for photopic vision>; stem:[K'], <for scotopic vision>; stem:[K_(\"mes\";m)], <for mesopic vision>; stem:[K_(10)], <for the CIE 10&deg; photopic photometric observer>; stem:[K_\"M\"], <for the CIE 1988 modified 2&deg; spectral luminous efficiency function for photopic vision>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm/W ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*kg^(-1)*m^(-2)*s^3 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-11.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "spectral luminous efficacy <specified photometric condition>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "K(lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-11.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-11.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-11.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """product of spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>) and maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>) for a specified photometric condition"""@en ;
  skos:note """Spectral luminous efficacy for photopic vision is expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
K(lambda) = K_\"m\" V(lambda)
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>) and stem:[lambda] is wavelength.

For scotopic and mesopic vision see <<cls-0.4>> and <<cls-0.5>>.

Symbols for different photometric conditions:

stem:[K(lambda)], <for photopic vision>; stem:[K'(lambda)], <for scotopic vision>; stem:[K_\"mes;m\"(lambda)], <for mesopic vision>; stem:[K_(10)(lambda)], <for the CIE 10&deg; photopic photometric observer>; stem:[K_\"M\"(lambda)], <for the CIE 1988 modified 2&deg; spectral luminous efficiency function for photopic vision>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm/W ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*kg^(-1)*m^(-2)*s^3 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-11.3-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "maximum luminous efficacy <specified photometric condition>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.3-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "K_\"m\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-11.3 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-11.3" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-11.3-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.3-0 ;
  skos:definition """maximum value of spectral luminous efficacy for a specified photometric condition"""@en ;
  skos:note """See also <<cls-0.4>> and <<cls-0.5>>.

The value of maximum luminous efficacy for photopic vision is calculated by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
K_\"m\" = (683)/(V(lambda_\"cd\")) \"unitsml(cd*sr*W^(-1))\" ~~ 683 \"unitsml(lm*W^(-1))\"
++++

where stem:[V(lambda)] is the spectral luminous efficiency for photopic vision and stem:[lambda_\"cd\"] is the wavelength in air corresponding to the frequency stem:[540*10^(12) \"unitsml(Hz)\"] specified in the definition of the SI unit candela.

Symbols for different photometric conditions:

stem:[K_\"m\"], <for photopic vision>; stem:[K'_\"m\"], <for scotopic vision>; stem:[K_\"m,mes;m\"], <for mesopic vision>; stem:[K_(\"m\",10)], <for the CIE 10&deg; photopic photometric observer>; stem:[K_\"m,M\"], <for the CIE 1988 modified 2&deg; spectral luminous efficiency function for photopic vision>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm/W ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*kg^(-1)*m^(-2)*s^3 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-11.4-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous efficacy of a source"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.4-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "eta_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.4-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(eta)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-11.4 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-11.4" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-11.4-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.4-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-11.4-1 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the luminous flux emitted and the power consumed by the source, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
eta_\"v\" = (Phi_\"v\")/P
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v\"] is luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[P] is the power (<<iso80000-4>>) consumed by the source
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm/W ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*kg^(-1)*m^(-2)*s^3 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-12-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous energy"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-12-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "DEPRECATED: quantity of light"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-12-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Q_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-12-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Q)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-12 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-12" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-12-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-12-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-12-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-12-1 ;
  skos:definition """energy of electromagnetic waves weighted by the spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>) multiplied by maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>) of a specified photometric condition"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminous energy for photopic vision is expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Q_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) Q_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[Q_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral radiant energy (<<t7-2.2>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>), stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>), and stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>).

Luminous energy can be emitted, transferred or received.

Luminous energy can be expressed by the time integral of the luminous flux (<<t7-13>>), stem:[Phi_\"v\"], over a given duration (<<iso80000-3>>), stem:[Delta t]

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Q_\"v\" = int_(Delta t) Phi_\"v\" \"d\"t
++++

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant energy\" (<<t7-2.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon energy\" (<<t7-19.2>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm*s ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*s ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-13-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous flux"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-13-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Phi_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-13-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Phi)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-13 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-13" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-13-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-13-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-13-1 ;
  skos:definition """change in luminous energy with time, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"v\" = (\"d\"Q_\"v\")/(\"d\"t)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"v\"] is the luminous energy (<<t7-12>>) emitted, transferred or received and stem:[t] is time (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminous flux is a quantity derived from the radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>), stem:[Phi_\"e\"], by evaluating the radiation according to its action upon the CIE standard photometric observer. (See <<cie017,locality:term=17-738>>.)

Luminous flux can be derived from the spectral radiant flux distribution by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is spectral radiant flux (<<t7-4.2>>), stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>) and stem:[lambda] is wavelength (<<iso80000-3>>).

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant flux\" (<<t7-4.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon flux\" (<<t7-20>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-14-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous intensity"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-14-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "I_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-14-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(I)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-14 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-14" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-14-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-14-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-14-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of luminous flux with respect to solid angle in a specified direction, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
I_\"v\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"v\")/(\"d\"Omega)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v\"] is the luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) emitted in a specified direction, and stem:[Omega] is the solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) containing that direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The definition holds strictly only for a point source.

The distribution of the luminous intensities as a function of the direction of emission, e.g. given by the polar angles stem:[(vartheta,varphi)], is used to determine the luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) within a certain solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) stem:[Omega] of a source:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"v\" = &#8748;_Omega I_\"v\" (vartheta,varphi)\"sin\" vartheta \"d\"varphi \"d\"vartheta
++++

Luminous intensity can be derived from the spectral radiant intensity distribution by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
I_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) I_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[I_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral radiant intensity (<<t7-5.2>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant intensity\" (<<t7-5.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon intensity\" (<<t7-21>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-15-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-15-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "L_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-15-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(L)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-15 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-15" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-15-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-15-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-15-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of luminous intensity with respect to projected area in a specified direction at a specified point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"v\" = (\"d\"I_\"v\")/(\"d\"A) 1/(\"cos\"alpha)
++++

where stem:[I_\"v\"] is luminous intensity (<<t7-14>>), stem:[A] is area (<<iso80000-3>>) and stem:[alpha] is the angle between the normal to the surface at the specified point and the specified direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminance can be derived from the spectral radiance distribution by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) L_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[L_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral radiance (<<t7-6.2>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>). See also <<cls-0.1>>.

Integral limits can be confined depending on the spectral sensitivity of the detectors used as a sensor.

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiance\" (<<t7-6.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon radiance\" (<<t7-22>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*m^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-16-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "illuminance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-16-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "E_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-16-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(E)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-16 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-16" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-16-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-16-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-16-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of incident luminous flux with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_\"v\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"v\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v\"] is luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) on which the luminous flux is incident
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Illuminance can be derived from the spectral irradiance distribution by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) E_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[E_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral irradiance (<<t7-7.2>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

Integral limits can be confined depending on the spectral sensitivity of the detectors used as a sensor.

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"irradiance\" (<<t7-7.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon irradiance\" (<<t7-23>>).

The quantity \"spherical illuminance\" is defined by the mean value of illuminance on the outer curved surface of a very small (real or imaginary) sphere at a point in space.

It can be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_(\"v\",0) = int_(4pi)L_\"v\"\"d\"Omega
++++

where stem:[Omega] is solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) and stem:[L_\"v\"] is luminance (<<t7-15>>).

It can be expressed by the quotient of the luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) of all the light incident on the outer surface of an infinitely small sphere centred at the given point, and the area (<<iso80000-3>>) of the diametrical cross-section of that sphere.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lx ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*m^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-17-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous exitance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-17-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "M_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-17-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(M)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-17 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-17" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-17-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-17-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-17-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of exiting luminous flux with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
M_\"v\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"v\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v\"] is luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) from which the luminous flux leaves
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminous exitance can be derived from the spectral radiant exitance distribution by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
M_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) M_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[M_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral radiant exitance (<<t7-8.2>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

Integral limits can be confined depending on the spectral sensitivity of the detectors used as a sensor.

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant exitance\" (<<t7-8.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon exitance\" (<<t7-24>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lm/m^2 ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*m^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-18-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous exposure"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-18-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "DEPRECATED: quantity of illumination"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-18-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "DEPRECATED: light exposure"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-18-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "H_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-18-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(H)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-18 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-18" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-18-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-18-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-18-2 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-18-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-18-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of incident luminous energy with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H_\"v\" = (\"d\"Q_\"v\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"v\"] is luminous energy (<<t7-12>>) and stem:[A] is the area on which the luminous energy is incident (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Luminous exposure can be derived from the spectral radiant exposure distribution by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H_\"v\" = K_\"m\" int_0^(oo) H_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda) V(lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[K_\"m\"] is maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>), stem:[H_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral radiant exposure (<<t7-9.2>>) at wavelength stem:[lambda] (<<iso80000-3>>), and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

Integral limits can be confined depending on the spectral sensitivity of the detectors used as a sensor.

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant exposure\" (<<t7-9.1>>). The corresponding quantity for photons is \"photon exposure\" (<<t7-25>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-lx*s ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-cd*sr*m^(-2)*s ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-19.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon number"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-19.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "number of photons"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-19.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "N_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-19.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-19.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-19.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-19.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-19.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of radiant energy and photon energy, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
N_\"p\" = (Q_\"e\")/(h nu)
++++

where stem:[Q_\"e\"] is radiant energy (<<t7-2.1>>), stem:[h] is the Planck constant (<<iso80000-1>>), and stem:[nu] is the frequency (<<iso80000-3>>) of the corresponding electromagnetic wave
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Photon number can also be expressed by the time integral of the photon flux (<<t7-20>>), stem:[Phi_\"p\"], over a given duration, stem:[Delta t],

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
N_\"p\" = int_(Delta t)Phi_\"p\" \"d\"t
++++
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-19.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon energy"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-19.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Q_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-19.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Q)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-19.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-19.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-19.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-19.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-19.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """product of the Planck constant and frequency, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Q_\"p\" = h nu
++++

where stem:[h] is the Planck constant (<<iso80000-1>>) and stem:[nu] is the frequency (<<iso80000-3>>) of the corresponding electromagnetic wave
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Photon energy can be emitted, transferred or received.

For monochromatic radiation, photon energy may be expressed by photon number (<<t7-19.1>>).

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant energy\" (<<t7-2.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous energy\" (<<t7-12>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-J ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg*m^2*s^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-20-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon flux"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-20-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Phi_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-20-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(Phi)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-20 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-20" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-20-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-20-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-20-1 ;
  skos:definition """rate of photon number per time interval, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"p\" = (\"d\"N_\"p\")/(\"d\"t)
++++

where stem:[N_\"p\"] is photon number (e.g. given by <<t7-19.1>>), transmitted or received, and stem:[t] is time (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Photon flux stem:[Phi_\"p\"] is related to radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>), stem:[Phi_\"e\"], of monochromatic radiation, by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"p\" = (Phi_\"e\")/(h nu)
++++

where stem:[h] is the Planck constant (<<iso80000-1>>), and stem:[nu] is the frequency (<<iso80000-3>>) of the corresponding electromagnetic wave.

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant flux\" (<<t7-4.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous flux\" (<<t7-13>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-s^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-21-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon intensity"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-21-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "I_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-21-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(I)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-21 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-21" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-21-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-21-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-21-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of photon flux with respect to solid angle in a specified direction, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
I_\"p\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"p\")/(\"d\"Omega)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"p\"] is the photon flux (<<t7-20>>) emitted in the given direction, and stem:[Omega] is the solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) containing that direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The distribution of the photon intensities as a function of the direction of emission, e.g. given by the polar angles stem:[(vartheta, varphi)], is used to determine the photon flux (<<t7-20>>) within a certain solid angle (<<iso80000-3>>) stem:[Omega] of a source:

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Phi_\"p\" = &#8748;_Omega I_\"p\" (vartheta,varphi) \"sin\" vartheta \"d\"varphi \"d\"vartheta
++++

The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant intensity\" (<<t7-5.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous intensity\" (<<t7-14>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-s^(-1)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-22-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon radiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-22-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "L_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-22-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(L)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-22 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-22" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-22-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-22-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-22-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of photon intensity with respect to projected area in a specified direction at a specified point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
L_\"p\" = (\"d\"I_\"p\")/(\"d\"A) 1/(\"cos\"alpha)
++++

where stem:[I_\"p\"] is photon intensity (<<t7-21>>), stem:[A] is area (<<iso80000-3>>) and stem:[alpha] the angle between the normal to the surface at the specified point and the specified direction
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiance\" (<<t7-6.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminance\" (<<t7-15>>)."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-2)*s^(-1)*sr^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-23-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon irradiance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-23-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "E_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-23-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(E)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-23 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-23" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-23-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-23-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-23-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of incident photon flux with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
E_\"p\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"p\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"p\"] is photon flux (<<t7-20>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) on which the photon flux is incident
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"irradiance\" (<<t7-7.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"illuminance\" (<<t7-16>>)."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-2)*s^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-24-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon exitance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-24-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "M_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-24-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(M)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-24 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-24" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-24-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-24-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-24-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of exiting photon flux with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
M_\"p\" = (\"d\"Phi_\"p\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"p\"] is photon flux (<<t7-20>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) from which the photon flux leaves
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant exitance\" (<<t7-8.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous exitance\" (<<t7-17>>)."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-2)*s^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-25-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "photon exposure"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-25-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "H_\"p\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-25-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(H)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-25 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-25" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-25-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-25-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-25-1 ;
  skos:definition """density of incident photon number with respect to area at a point on a real or imaginary surface, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
H_\"p\" = (\"d\"N_\"p\")/(\"d\"A)
++++

where stem:[N_\"p\"] is photon number (<<t7-19.1>>) and stem:[A] is the area (<<iso80000-3>>) on which the photons are incident
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The corresponding radiometric quantity is \"radiant exposure\" (<<t7-9.1>>). The corresponding photometric quantity is \"luminous exposure\" (<<t7-18>>)."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-2) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-26.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "tristimulus values for the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric observer"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-26.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "X, Y, Z"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-26.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-26.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-26.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-26.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """amounts of the three reference colour stimuli in the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric system, required to match the colour of the stimulus considered"""@en ;
  skos:note """For a given colour stimulus described by the colour stimulus function stem:[Phi_lambda(lambda)] of a radiometric quantity,

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
X = k int_0^(oo) Phi_lambda (lambda) bar x (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Y = k int_0^(oo) Phi_lambda (lambda) bar y (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Z = k int_0^(oo) Phi_lambda (lambda) bar z (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[bar x (lambda)], stem:[bar y (lambda)], stem:[bar z (lambda)] are the CIE colour-matching functions for the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric observer (2&deg; observer) (<<t7-27.1>>).

For sources, stem:[k] may be chosen as stem:[k = K_\"m\"] where stem:[K_\"m\"] is the maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>) so that stem:[Y = L_\"v\"] (<<t7-15>>) and the unit of stem:[X], stem:[Y], stem:[Z] is [stem:[\"unitsml(cd*m^(-2))\"]].

For object colours, stem:[varphi_lambda(lambda)] is given by one of the three products

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
varphi_lambda(lambda) = S_lambda(lambda) * {(rho(lambda)),(tau(lambda)),(beta(lambda)):}
++++

where stem:[S_lambda(lambda)] is the relative spectral distribution of a quantity characterizing the source illuminating the object, stem:[rho(lambda)] is the spectral reflectance, stem:[tau(lambda)] is the spectral transmittance, stem:[beta(lambda)] is the spectral radiance factor, and stem:[k] is chosen to be

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
k = 100 // int_0^(oo) S_lambda (lambda) bar y (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

Integral limits can be confined depending on the spectral sensitivity of the detectors used as a sensor. In this case, the unit of stem:[X], stem:[Y], stem:[Z] is [1].
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-stem:["see Remark"] ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-26.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "tristimulus values for the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric observer"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-26.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "X_(10), Y_(10), Z_(10)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-26.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-26.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-26.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-26.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """amounts of the three reference colour stimuli in the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric system, required to match the colour of the stimulus considered"""@en ;
  skos:note """For a given colour stimulus described by the colour stimulus function stem:[varphi_lambda(lambda)] of a radiometric quantity,

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
X_(10) = k int_0^(oo) varphi_lambda(lambda) bar x_(10) (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Y_(10) = k int_0^(oo) varphi_lambda(lambda) bar y_(10) (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
Z_(10) = k int_0^(oo) varphi_lambda(lambda) bar z_(10) (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

where stem:[bar x_(10)(lambda)], stem:[bar y_(10)(lambda)], stem:[bar z_(10)(lambda)] are the CIE colour-matching functions for the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric observer (10&deg; observer) (<<t7-27.2>>).

For sources, stem:[k] may be chosen as stem:[k = K_(10)] where stem:[K_(10)] is the maximum luminous efficacy (<<t7-11.3>>) of the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric observer so that stem:[Y_(10) = L_(10)] and the unit of stem:[X], stem:[Y], stem:[Z] is [stem:[\"unitsml(cd*m^(-2))\"]].

For object colours, stem:[varphi_lambda(lambda)] is given by one of the three products

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
varphi_lambda (lambda) = S_lambda (lambda) * {(rho(lambda)),(tau(lambda)),(beta(lambda)):}
++++

where stem:[S_lambda(lambda)] is the relative spectral distribution of a quantity characterizing the source illuminating the object, stem:[rho(lambda)] is the spectral reflectance, stem:[tau(lambda)] is the spectral transmittance, stem:[beta(lambda)] is the spectral radiance factor, and stem:[k] is chosen to be

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
k = 100 // int_0^(oo) S_lambda (lambda) bar y (lambda) \"d\"lambda
++++

Integral limits can be confined depending on the spectral sensitivity of the detectors used as a sensor. In this case, the unit of stem:[X], stem:[Y], stem:[Z] is [1].
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-stem:["see Remark"] ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-27.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "CIE colour-matching functions for the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric observer"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-27.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "bar x(lambda), bar y(lambda), bar z(lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-27.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-27.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-27.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-27.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """functions stem:[bar x(lambda)], stem:[bar y(lambda)], stem:[bar z(lambda)] in the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric system"""@en ;
  skos:note """Values of stem:[bar x(lambda)], stem:[bar y(lambda)] and stem:[bar z(lambda)] are defined in the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric system (2&deg; observer) -- applicable to fields of observation of angular opening from 1&deg; to 4&deg;."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-27.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "CIE colour-matching functions for the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric observer"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-27.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "bar x_(10)(lambda), bar y_(10)(lambda), bar z_(10)(lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-27.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-27.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-27.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-27.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """functions stem:[bar x_(10)(lambda)], stem:[bar y_(10)(lambda)], stem:[bar z_(10)(lambda)] in the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric system"""@en ;
  skos:note """Values of stem:[bar x_(10)(lambda)], stem:[bar y_(10)(lambda)] and stem:[bar z_(10)(lambda)] are defined in the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric system (10&deg; observer) -- applicable to fields of observation with angles greater than 4&deg;."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-28.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "chromaticity coordinates in the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric system"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-28.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "x, y, z"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-28.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-28.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-28.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-28.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """coordinates expressing the quotients of each of a set of three tristimulus values for the CIE 1931 standard colorimetric observer (<<t7-26.1>>) and their sum, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
x = X // (X+Y+Z),
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
y = Y // (X+Y+Z),
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
z = Z // (X+Y+Z)
++++
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Since stem:[x + y + z = 1], two variables are sufficient to express chromaticity."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-28.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "chromaticity coordinates in the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric system"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-28.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "x_(10), y_(10), z_(10)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-28.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-28.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-28.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-28.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """coordinates expressing the quotients of each of a set of three tristimulus values for the CIE 1964 standard colorimetric observer (<<t7-26.2>>) and their sum, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
x_(10) = X_(10) // (X_(10) + Y_(10) + Z_(10)),
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
y_(10) = Y_(10) // (X_(10) + Y_(10) + Z_(10)),
++++

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
z_(10) = Z_(10) // (X_(10) + Y_(10) + Z_(10))
++++
"""@en ;
  skos:note """Since stem:[x_(10) + y_(10) + z_(10) = 1], two variables are sufficient to express chromaticity."""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-29.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "colour temperature"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-29.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "T_\"c\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-29.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-29.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-29.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-29.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """temperature of a Planckian radiator whose radiation has the same chromaticity as that of a given stimulus"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-K ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-29.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "correlated colour temperature"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-29.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "T_\"cp\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-29.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-29.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-29.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-29.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """temperature of a Planckian radiator having the chromaticity nearest the chromaticity associated with the given spectral distribution on a modified 1976 CIE Uniform Chromaticity Scale (UCS) diagram where

stem:[u'], stem:[2/3 v'] are the coordinates of the Planckian locus and the test stimulus
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-K ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-30.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "emissivity"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-30.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "epsilon"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-30.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "epsilon_\"T\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-30.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-30.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-30.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-30.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-30.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the radiant exitance of a radiator and the radiant exitance of a Planckian radiator at the same temperature, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
epsilon = M/M_\"b\"
++++

where stem:[M] is the radiant exitance (<<t7-8.1>>) of a thermal radiator and stem:[M_\"b\"] is the radiant exitance of a Planckian radiator at the same temperature (<<iso80000-5>>)
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-30.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "emissivity at a specified wavelength"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-30.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "epsilon(lambda)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-30.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-30.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-30.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-30.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the radiant exitance of a radiator at a specified wavelength and the radiant exitance of a Planckian radiator at the same temperature and at the same wavelength, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
epsilon(lambda) = M(lambda) // M_\"b\"(lambda)
++++

where stem:[M(lambda)] is the radiant exitance (<<t7-8.1>>) of a thermal radiator at a specified wavelength and stem:[M_\"b\"(lambda)] is the radiant exitance of a Planckian radiator at the same temperature at a specified wavelength (<<iso80000-3>>)
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-31.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "absorptance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "a"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-31.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-31.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-31.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of absorbed radiant flux and incident radiant flux, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha = Phi_\"a\"/Phi_\"m\"
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"a\"] is absorbed radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) and stem:[Phi_\"m\"] is incident radiant flux
"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case \"spectral\" is added before the quantity name.

Due to energy conservation, stem:[alpha + rho + tau = 1] except when polarized radiation is observed, where stem:[rho] is reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>) and stem:[tau] is transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-31.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous absorptance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-31.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-31.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-31.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of absorbed luminous flux and incident luminous flux, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"v\" = (Phi_(\"v,a\"))/(Phi_\"v,m\")
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v,a\"] is absorbed luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[Phi_\"v,m\"] is incident luminous flux
"""@en ;
  skos:note """From spectral absorptance, stem:[alpha(lambda)], luminous absorptance can be calculated by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"v\" = (int_0^(oo) alpha(lambda) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda) V(lambda) \"d\"lambda)/(int_0^(oo) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda) V(lambda) \"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is spectral radiant flux (or relative spectral distribution) of the source, and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

See also <<t7-31.1>>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-31.3-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "reflectance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.3-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "rho"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-31.3 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-31.3" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-31.3-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.3-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of reflected radiant flux and incident radiant flux, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
rho = Phi_\"r\"/Phi_\"m\"
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"r\"] is reflected radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) and stem:[Phi_\"m\"] is incident radiant flux
"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before the quantity name.

Due to energy conservation, stem:[alpha + rho + tau = 1] except when polarized radiation is observed, where stem:[alpha] is absorptance (<<t7-31.1>>) and stem:[tau] is transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-31.4-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous reflectance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.4-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "rho_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-31.4 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-31.4" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-31.4-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.4-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of reflected luminous flux and incident luminous flux, is expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
rho_\"v\" = (Phi_(\"v,r\"))/(Phi_\"v,m\")
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v,r\"] is reflected luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[Phi_\"v,m\"] is incident luminous flux
"""@en ;
  skos:note """From spectral reflectance, stem:[rho(lambda)], luminous reflectance can be calculated by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
rho_\"v\" = (int_0^(oo) rho(lambda) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda)/(int_0^(oo) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is spectral radiant flux (or relative spectral distribution) of the source, and stem:[V(lambda)] is spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

See also <<t7-31.3>>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-31.5-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "transmittance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.5-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "tau"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.5-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "T"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-31.5 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-31.5" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-31.5-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.5-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.5-1 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of transmitted radiant flux and incident radiant flux, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
tau = Phi_\"t\"/Phi_\"m\"
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"t\"] is transmitted radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) and stem:[Phi_\"m\"] is incident radiant flux
"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before the quantity name.

Due to energy conservation, stem:[alpha + rho + tau = 1] except when polarized radiation is observed, where stem:[alpha] is absorptance (<<t7-31.1>>) and stem:[rho] is reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>).
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-31.6-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminous transmittance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.6-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "tau_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-31.6 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-31.6" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-31.6-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-31.6-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of transmitted luminous flux and incident luminous flux, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
tau_\"v\" = (Phi_\"v,t\")/(Phi_\"v,m\")
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"v,t\"] is transmitted luminous flux (<<t7-13>>) and stem:[Phi_\"v,m\"] is luminous flux of the incident radiation
"""@en ;
  skos:note """From the spectral transmittance stem:[tau(lambda)], luminous transmittance can be calculated by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
tau_\"v\" = (int_0^(oo) tau(lambda) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda)/(int_0^(oo) Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)V(lambda)\"d\"lambda)
++++

where stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)] is the spectral radiant flux (or relative spectral distribution) of the source, and stem:[V(lambda)] is the spectral luminous efficiency (<<t7-10.2>>).

See also <<t7-31.5>>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "transmittance optical density"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "optical density"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "transmittance density"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-3 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "decadic absorbance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "D"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "A_(10)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.1-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "D_tau"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-32.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-32.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-2 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-32.1-3 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.1-2 ;
  skos:definition """logarithm to base 10 of the reciprocal of the transmittance, stem:[tau] (<<t7-31.5>>)"""@en ;
  skos:note """If defined in terms of wavelength, the optical density can be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
A_(10)(lambda) = -\"lg\"[tau(lambda)\\]
++++

where stem:[tau(lambda)] is the transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>) in terms of wavelength.

In spectroscopy, the name \"absorbance stem:[A_(10)]\" is generally used.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-32.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Napierian absorbance"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "A_\"n\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "B"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-32.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-32.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-32.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-32.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """natural (Napierian) logarithm of the reciprocal of the transmittance, stem:[tau] (<<t7-31.5>>)"""@en ;
  skos:note """If defined in terms of wavelength, the Napierian absorbance can be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
A_\"n\"(lambda) = B(lambda) = -\"ln\"[tau(lambda)\\]
++++

It can also be expressed as

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
A_\"n\"(lambda) = l alpha(lambda)
++++

where stem:[alpha] is linear absorption coefficient (<<t7-35.2>>) and stem:[l] is length (<<iso80000-3>>) traversed.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-33.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "radiance factor"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "beta_\"e\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(beta)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-33.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-33.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-33.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the radiance of a surface element in a specified direction and the radiance of the perfect reflecting diffuser or perfect transmitting diffuser identically irradiated and viewed, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
beta_\"e\" = (L_\"e,n\")/(L_\"e,d\")
++++

where stem:[L_\"e,n\"] is the radiance (<<t7-6.1>>) of a surface element in a given direction and stem:[L_\"e,d\"] is the radiance of the perfect reflecting or transmitting diffuser identically irradiated and viewed
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The definition holds for a surface element of a non-self-radiating medium, in a given direction and under specified conditions of irradiation.

Radiance factor is equivalent to reflectance factor (<<t7-34>>) or luminance factor (<<t7-33.2>>) when the cone angle is infinitely small, and is equivalent to reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>) when the cone angle is stem:[2pi \"unitsml(sr)\"]. These quantities are also defined spectrally and called spectral radiance factor stem:[beta(lambda)] and spectral reflectance factor stem:[R(lambda)].

The ideal isotropic (Lambertian) diffuser with reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>) or transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>) equal to 1 is called \"perfect diffuser\".
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-33.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "luminance factor"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "beta_\"v\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "(beta)"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-33.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-33.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-33.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-33.2-1 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the luminance of a surface element in a specified direction and the luminance of the perfect reflecting diffuser or perfect transmitting diffuser identically illuminated and viewed, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
beta_\"v\" = (L_\"v,n\")/(L_\"v,d\")
++++

where stem:[L_\"v,n\"] is the luminance (<<t7-15>>) of a surface element in a given direction and stem:[L_\"v,d\"] is the luminance of the perfect reflecting or transmitting diffuser identically illuminated and viewed
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The definition holds for a surface element of a non-luminous medium, in a given direction and under specified conditions of irradiation.

This quantity is also defined spectrally and is called \"spectral luminance factor\".

For the analogous radiant quantity \"radiance factor\", see <<t7-33.1>>.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-34-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "reflectance factor"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-34-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "R"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-34 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-34" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-34-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-34-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the flux reflected in the directions delimited by a given cone with apex at a surface element and the flux reflected in the same directions by a perfect reflecting diffuser identically irradiated or illuminated, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
R=Phi_\"n\"/Phi_\"d\"
++++

where stem:[Phi_\"n\"] is the flux reflected in the directions delimited by a given cone and stem:[Phi_\"d\"] is the flux reflected in the same directions by an identically irradiated diffuser of reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>) equal to 1
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The flux can be a radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) or a luminous flux (<<t7-13>>).

The definition holds for a surface element, for the part of the reflected radiation contained in a given cone with apex at the surface element, and for incident radiation of given spectral composition, polarization and geometric distribution.

Reflectance factor is equivalent to radiance factor (<<t7-33.1>>) or luminance factor (<<t7-33.2>>) when the cone angle is infinitely small, and is equivalent to reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>) when the cone angle is stem:[2pi \"unitsml(sr)\"]. These quantities are also defined spectrally and called spectral radiance factor stem:[beta(lambda)] and spectral reflectance factor stem:[R(lambda)].

The ideal isotropic (Lambertian) diffuser with reflectance (<<t7-31.3>>) or transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>) equal to 1 is called a perfect diffuser.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-1 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-35.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "linear attenuation coefficient"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:term-t7-35.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "linear extinction coefficient <radiometry>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "mu"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.1-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "mu_\"l\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-35.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-35.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-35.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-35.1-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.1-1 ;
  skos:definition """relative decrease in radiant flux caused by absorption and scattering"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before this quantity name.

The spectral linear attenuation coefficient can be expressed by the relative decrease in the spectral radiant flux, stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)], with respect to propagation length, stem:[l], of a collimated beam at a point in an absorbing and scattering medium

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
mu(lambda) = 1/(Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)) (\"d\"Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda))/(\"d\"l)
++++

Similarly, luminous and photon quantities can be defined.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-35.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "linear absorption coefficient <radiometry>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha_\"l\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-1 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "a_\"l\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-2 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-35.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-35.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-35.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-1 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-35.2-2 ;
  skos:definition """relative decrease in radiant flux (<<t7-4.1>>) caused by absorption"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before this quantity name.

The spectral linear absorption coefficient can be expressed by the relative decrease in the spectral radiant flux, stem:[Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)], with respect to propagation length, stem:[l], of a collimated beam at a point in an absorbing medium

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"l\"(lambda) = 1/(Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda)) (\"d\"Phi_(\"e\",lambda)(lambda))/(\"d\"l)
++++

It can also be expressed as a function of transmittance (<<t7-31.5>>).

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"l\" = -\"ln\"(tau)//l = A_\"n\"//l
++++

The linear absorption coefficient is that part of the linear attenuation coefficient (<<t7-35.1>>) that is due to absorption. Scattering might also contribute.

Similarly, luminous and photon quantities can be defined.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-36.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "mass attenuation coefficient <radiometry>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-36.1-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "mu_\"m\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-36.1 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-36.1" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-36.1-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-36.1-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the linear attenuation coefficient (<<t7-35.1>>), stem:[mu], and the mass density (<<iso80000-4>>), stem:[rho], of the medium"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before this quantity name, which can be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
mu_\"m\"(lambda) = (mu(lambda))/rho_\"m\"
++++

Similarly, luminous and photon quantities can be defined.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-kg^(-1)*m^2 ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-36.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "mass absorption coefficient <radiometry>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-36.2-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "alpha_\"m\""@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-36.2 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-36.2" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-36.2-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-36.2-0 ;
  skos:definition """quotient of the linear absorption coefficient (<<t7-35.2>>), stem:[alpha], and the mass density (<<iso80000-4>>), stem:[rho], of the medium"""@en ;
  skos:note """This quantity is also defined spectrally in terms of wavelength, in which case, \"spectral\" is added before this quantity name, which can be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
alpha_\"m\"(lambda) = (alpha(lambda))/rho_\"m\"
++++

Similarly, luminous and photon quantities can be defined.
"""@en ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .

isoiec80000:term-t7-37-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "molar absorption coefficient <radiometry>"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t7-37-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "chi"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t7-37 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "7-37" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t7-37-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t7-37-0 ;
  skos:definition """product of linear absorption coefficient and molar volume, expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
chi = alpha V_\"m\"
++++

where stem:[alpha] is linear absorption coefficient (<<t7-35.2>>) and stem:[V_\"m\"] is molar volume (<<iso80000-9>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """The molar absorption coefficient can also be expressed by

[stem%unnumbered]
++++
chi=alpha c
++++

where stem:[c] is amount-of-substance concentration (<<iso80000-9>>).

Similarly, luminous and photon quantities can be defined.
"""@en ;
  isoiec80000:hasUnit isoiec80000:unit-m^2*mol^(-1) ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-7 .
